---
import { arteImperceptibleBook } from "../data/featured";
---

<section
  id="about"
  class="scroll-mt-28 border-t border-stone-800/95 bg-[#151312]"
  aria-labelledby="about-heading"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-14 sm:px-6 lg:py-20">
    <h2 id="about-heading" class="font-display text-[1.875rem] font-semibold tracking-tight text-[#fcf6ee]">
      About
    </h2>
    <div class="mt-5 max-w-2xl space-y-5 text-[0.9625rem] leading-[1.75] text-stone-400">
      <p>
        I&apos;m a data scientist and software engineer focused on predictive modelling and recruiting analytics in football.
        I care about artefacts that survive hand-off: reproducible notebooks, observable services, dashboards scouts reopen without needing fresh context every week.
      </p>
      <p>
        Today that lands mainly at{" "}
        <strong class="font-semibold text-stone-200">Levante UD</strong>{" "}(research collaborator on similarity-heavy scouting work) and at{" "}
        <strong class="font-semibold text-stone-200">Fever</strong>, where I ship Python services and ingestion at real traffic volumes — Postgres tuning included.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p>
          Off the codebase: placing second at the{" "}
          <strong class="font-semibold text-stone-200">Aigües de Barcelona Data Challenge</strong>{" "}and credited participation alongside Levante in Alejandro Losa Brito&apos;s{" "}
          <a
            class="font-semibold italic text-amber-200 underline decoration-amber-500/55 underline-offset-[3px] transition hover:text-amber-50"
            href={arteImperceptibleBook.amazonUrl}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            {arteImperceptibleBook.titleShort}</a>.
        </p>
        <p class="rounded-md border border-stone-700/95 bg-[#141210]/90 px-[0.875rem] py-[0.6875rem] font-sans text-[0.85rem] leading-relaxed text-stone-500">
          Scout-facing book on imperceptible detail in modern football —
          paperback in Spanish (<span lang="es">scouting · match breakdown · club workflows</span>), released April&nbsp;2026.
          Listing:{" "}
          <a
            class="font-semibold text-amber-200 underline decoration-amber-500/55 underline-offset-[3px] hover:text-[#fff7ed]"
            href={arteImperceptibleBook.amazonUrl}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Amazon.es&nbsp;<span aria-hidden="true">·</span> ISBN&nbsp;979-1387868925
          </a>
          <span aria-hidden="true">&nbsp;(↗)</span>
          .
        </p>
      </div>
      <p class="border-l-2 border-amber-500/60 pl-4 text-[0.8875rem] leading-relaxed text-stone-500">
        B.Sc. Computer Engineering (data science),{" "}
        <strong class="font-medium text-stone-400">UPF · 2021–2025</strong>
        · thesis graded Excellent with Honors — same lineage as{" "}
        <em>Stars of the Future</em> listed in Projects.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
